rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week is filled with work and one social activity, so I see it continuing in a pretty typical fashion conducive to my current routine. Work has been going well even during stressful situations, so I see no direct problems there. I'm attending a social gathering over the weekend so that will positively affect the rest of my week.
critical_positive: I think because we shared some common demographics, we were able to easily connect when discussing current issues and interests. My partner was very receptive and seemed to show a genuine interest in the topics we discussed. I know I personally tend to talk a lot, so I tried not to dominate the conversation. However, it was very easy to listen to her and there were very few points where I felt like the conversation lagged or got stuck.
critical_negative: Starting the conversation was a bit awkward but that was to be expected since we were total strangers. I reverted back to basic ice breakers, which aren't always the most interesting but they do work to get things going. We did spend a lot of time discussing how the pandemic has affected our daily lives, but that's really all people can talk about these days.

rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of the week will go well. I get paid tomorrow, and I plan to have a small party with my boyfriend and some friends. I also think I might go out to dinner with my boyfriend somewhere nice. Today makes me a little anxious, as I have a class tonight with a big assignment due, but as long as I can get through it I will be okay.
critical_positive: She asked a lot of questions and shared information about herself. I think that the conversation flowed well, and we found a few things in common. Since the world has been experiencing a global pandemic, that helped us find common ground to build a long, full conversation and share our experiences more smoothly.
critical_negative: She asked far more questions than I did, which made me worry about her not feeling listened to. I also believe she may have been bored at some points in the conversation, as she glanced at the time a few times throughout the call. I think that we also had difficulty trusting each other at first.
